public class ImageUrlCodingStrategy
extends org.apache.wicket.request.target.basic.URIRequestTargetUrlCodingStrategy

Strategy to find resources based on a simple URL path. This allows for example a directory of images to be found by URLs in your markup file that begin with a known prefix. For instance, if you have images under an "img" directory in a "theme directory", and have code like this in Application.init(): 

     getResourceSettings().addResourceFolder("/mythemedir");
     mount(new ImageUrlCodingStrategy("img"));
then an image reference in your markup file like this 
     <img src="img/logos/logo.png"/>
will refer to an image in that them directory (/mythemedir/img/etc), rather than Wicket's default of looking for the image relative to the current HTML markup file.
